qas.question: Who else joins Armenia in the CSTO?

answers.text: Belarus, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Russia, Tajikistan and Uzbekistan

qas.question: When did Armenia remove its peacekeepers from Iraq?

context: Armenia is member of <a0_0>Collective Security Treaty Organisation<a0_0/> (CSTO) along with <a2_0>Belarus, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Russia, Tajikistan and Uzbekistan<a2_0/>. It participates in NATO's Partnership for Peace (PiP) program and is in a NATO organisation called <a1_0>Euro-Atlantic Partnership Council<a1_0/> (EAPC). Armenia has engaged in a peacekeeping mission in Kosovo as part of non-NATO KFOR troops under Greek command. Armenia also had 46 members of its military peacekeeping forces as a part of the Coalition Forces in Iraq War until <a3_0>October 2008<a3_0/>.
